# CLAUDE.local.md

Personal notes for this repo (gitignored).

## Context

Solo hobby project. I know the codebase — no need to over-explain basics or hedge.

## How to work with me

- Be terse. Skip end-of-turn recaps; the diff speaks for itself.
- Before changing approach mid-task, surface the tradeoff in one line so I can redirect.
- For non-trivial multi-file changes, propose a short plan before diving in.

## Surface your reasoning

Thinking tokens are hidden from me, so I can't see your rationale by default. Make it visible in regular output:

- Before any non-trivial tool call (edits, multi-file reads, refactors), write a 1-line "why" — what you're about to do and the reasoning behind it.
- When choosing between approaches, state the options you considered and why you picked one. One line each is enough.
- When you reject an obvious alternative, say so briefly ("not using X because Y").
- When diagnosing a bug, state your hypothesis before testing it.
- Keep it terse — a sentence, not a paragraph. The point is visibility, not verbosity.
